&lt;p&gt;Translations from [[Adams, 2DoT]]: &lt;b&gt;a2&lt;/b&gt; "for the workers barley (meal) went, three deciliters; for the &lt;i&gt;tällaikantsas&lt;/i&gt; double the flour" [315].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is possible that THT 443 and THT 444 fit together almost exactly as mounted in the frame, with THT 443 a3 and THT 444 a1 being the same line /// &lt;i&gt;(saṅ)kästere (ś)l(acaṃd)r(e śarsa) ¤&lt;/i&gt; . The horizontally mirrored shapes of the fragments then result from having been stored as furled scroll. –Martin (Tue, 2019-01-15, 23:32:17 (CET))&lt;/p&gt;</item>
